 <item> <title>U.S. Department of Education Awards More Than $16.2 Million in Grants to Improve School Leadership at Lowest-Performing Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/us-department-education-awards-more-162-million-grants-improve-school-leadership-lowest-performing-schools</link>
 <description>The U.S. Department of Education awarded more than $16.2 million to eight grantees to develop and implement or enhance and implement a leadership pipeline that selects, prepares, places, supports and retains school leaders or leadership teams at low-performing schools that need the most help in meeting the academic needs of its students.</description>
